{"id": "afq1665702786735", "title": "Add User-Defined Options to IDE Menus", "breadcrumbs": ["Uniface IDE", "Customizing the Uniface IDE", "Add User-Defined Options to IDE Menus"], "url": "https://docs.rocketsoftware.com/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/afq1665702786735.html", "html": "<html><body><header class=\"zDocsTopicPageHead\"><h1 class=\"css-g931ng\">Add User-Defined Options to IDE Menus</h1><div class=\"zDocsTopicActions\" role=\"list\"><div class=\"zDocsBundlePagination\" data-testid=\"next-prev-container\" role=\"listitem\"><div class=\"zDocsPrevTopicButton zDocsPrevTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Previous: Add User-Defined Worksheets to IDE Editors\" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Previous: Add User-Defined Worksheets to IDE Editors\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vjz1665702778665.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-prev\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-prev\"></use></svg></a></span></div><div class=\"zDocsNextTopicButton zDocsNextTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Next: Adding user-defined keyboard shortcuts in the IDE\" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Next: Adding user-defined keyboard shortcuts in the IDE\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jwc1695725497353.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></a></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsMyDocsMenu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Add to My Topics\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Add to My Topics\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" id=\"addToMyDocsDropdownTrigger\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/afq1665702786735.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/afq1665702786735.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/afq1665702786735.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 19, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104afq1665702786735.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/afq1665702786735.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/afq1665702786735.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"afq1665702786735\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Add User-Defined\n      Options to IDE Menus</h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To integrate custom functionality into the Uniface IDE, you can use the IDE Menu\n      Plug-In API to create components that define the desired menu options and implement the\n      actions performed by these options. You must then add the components to the Uniface IDE\n      resources and configure the IDE to use them.</p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"afq1665702786735__li_d1820e1_d1821e1_d1822e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"afq1665702786735__p_d4409e1_d4410e1_d4411e1\">Create at least one component that implements the\n               following operations to specify the menu options to be added.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afq1665702786735__li_d1823e1_d1824e1_d1825e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xju1665702763689.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xju1665702763689.html\" title=\"Return the version number of the IDE Menu Plug-In API used by this component.\">getVersion</a>—return the version number of the API that you have programmed for. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afq1665702786735__li_d1826e1_d1827e1_d1828e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ewi1665702763758.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ewi1665702763758.html\" title=\"Return a Struct with the menu options to be added to the IDE's Main Menu ( ≡ ).\">getGlobalMenuOptions</a>—return the menu options for the Main Menu ( ≡ )).</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afq1665702786735__li_d1829e1_d1830e1_d1831e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vrg1665702763825.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vrg1665702763825.html\" title=\"Return a Struct with the menu items to add to the Actions menu of an object editor.\">getEditorMenuOptions</a>—return the menu options for the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Actions</span> menu in\n                     object editors. These options can be dynamic, based on the type and/or name of\n                     the current object. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">The IDE calls these operations at run time, so it is possible to populate menus\n                  dynamically, based on data or other circumstances that can be looked up just\n                  before the menu is displayed.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"afq1665702786735__li_d1832e1_d1833e1_d1834e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create the callback components that implement the menu actions. For each operation called by a menu option, include the appropriate menu option parameters. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ina1665702763956.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ina1665702763956.html\" title=\"Menu callback operations define the action that is taken when a user selects the associated menu option in the IDE. The names of callback operations are user-defined, but the interface is fixed.\">Menu Callback Operations</a>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"afq1665702786735__li_d1835e1_d1836e1_d1837e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally, package your custom components into a Uniface archive file.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"afq1665702786735__li_d1838e1_d1839e1_d1840e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Uniface IDE assignment file, specify the location of the components in the\n               [RESOURCES] section. You can specify a UAR, or the <span class=\"ph filepath\">resources</span>\n               directory where the compiled components are located. For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104afq1665702786735_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"afq1665702786735__codeblock_iy3_3xl_mzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[RESOURCES]\n; D:/unifaceData/project/resources ; dir where IDE puts compiled components\nD:/uniface10/project/USERMENUS.UAR \nusys:ide.uar\nusys:ide_messages.uar</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"afq1665702786735__li_d1841e1_d1842e1_d1843e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"afq1665702786735__p_d4412e1_d4413e1_d4414e1\">In the Uniface IDE assignment file, specify the name of the components that return the menu options using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">IDE_DEFINE_USERMENUS</code> logical.\n To specify a separator between the menu options provided by different components, use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">_sep_</code>keyword. For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104afq1665702786735_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"afq1665702786735__codeblock_npd_lxl_mzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[LOGICALS]\nIDE_DEFINE_USERMENUS = USERMENU1, _sep_, USERMENU2, USERMENU3</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"afq1665702786735__p_d4415e1_d4416e1_d4417e1\">There will always be a separator between the IDE options and the first user option.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/glu1665702763543.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>IDE Menu Plug-Ins</a><p>Menu plug-ins are components that the Uniface IDE calls to dynamically add custom menu items to the IDE's Main Menu ( ≡ ) and to the Actions menu of editors. They let you integrate functionality that is specific to your environment or workflow into the IDE.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Add User-Defined Options to IDE Menus Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 19, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Add User-Defined Options to IDE Menus To integrate custom functionality into the Uniface IDE, you can use the IDE Menu Plug-In API to create components that define the desired menu options and implement the actions performed by these options. You must then add the components to the Uniface IDE resources and configure the IDE to use them. Create at least one component that implements the following operations to specify the menu options to be added. getVersion —return the version number of the API that you have programmed for. getGlobalMenuOptions —return the menu options for the Main Menu ( ≡ )). getEditorMenuOptions —return the menu options for the Actions menu in object editors. These options can be dynamic, based on the type and/or name of the current object. The IDE calls these operations at run time, so it is possible to populate menus dynamically, based on data or other circumstances that can be looked up just before the menu is displayed. Create the callback components that implement the menu actions. For each operation called by a menu option, include the appropriate menu option parameters. For more information, see Menu Callback Operations . Optionally, package your custom components into a Uniface archive file. In the Uniface IDE assignment file, specify the location of the components in the [RESOURCES] section. You can specify a UAR, or the resources directory where the compiled components are located. For example: Explain this code [RESOURCES] ; D:/unifaceData/project/resources ; dir where IDE puts compiled components D:/uniface10/project/USERMENUS.UAR usys:ide.uar usys:ide_messages.uar Copy In the Uniface IDE assignment file, specify the name of the components that return the menu options using the IDE_DEFINE_USERMENUS logical. To specify a separator between the menu options provided by different components, use the _sep_ keyword. For example: Explain this code [LOGICALS] IDE_DEFINE_USERMENUS = USERMENU1, _sep_, USERMENU2, USERMENU3 Copy There will always be a separator between the IDE options and the first user option. Related Links IDE Menu Plug-Ins Menu plug-ins are components that the Uniface IDE calls to dynamically add custom menu items to the IDE's Main Menu ( ≡ ) and to the Actions menu of editors. They let you integrate functionality that is specific to your environment or workflow into the IDE. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}